President Cyril Ramaphosa and KwaZulu Natal Premier Sihle Zikalala. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa is set to visit KwaZulu Natal to assess the province’s COVID-19 response. KwaZulu Natal Premier Sihle Zikalala will accompany Ramaphosa as a tour guide to sites identified as COVID-19 facilities. The president will commence his programme at Archie Gumede House in Mayville, Durban, where he will engage with the provincial government and stakeholders on the province's response strategies and progress being made to flatten the curve of the coronavirus pandemic. He will then proceed to the Dr Pixley Isaka Seme Provincial Hospital in KwaMashu, north of Durban, which is one of the hospitals designated to manage the coronavirus. READ: SA starts coronavirus trial of TB vaccine Ramaphosa’s programme will conclude with a walkabout at the Agricultural Royal Showgrounds in Pietermaritzburg which has been designated as a quarantine or isolation facility for patients. South Africa’s coronavirus death toll stands at 138 which with 35 of those fatalities coming from KZN. The province records at least 10 new cases daily with the epicentre in eThekwini being a major concern. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.